27T01:42:54.000Z","msg":"A wavy line in front of a chord means to play the notes one after another beginning at the bottom. A rolled chord is a type of broken chord. It's a chord whose notes are played quickly in order, as opposed to simultaneously; to give a chord a harp-like effect. Use second and fourth fingers on all broken thirds in the right hand and fourth, third, second and first fingers on F sharp, G, G sharp and A in the left hand."}]}